# CodeDocGenerator

A Python CLI tool for generating AI-powered code documentation and visualizations.

## Installation
```bash
pip install code_doc_generator

Usage
bash

# Generate README.md with project documentation
code-doc generate docs /path/to/project

# Generate project structure visualization
code-doc generate structure /path/to/project

# Generate dependency graphs for a file (saved as ZIP)
code-doc generate graphs /path/to/file.py
Features
Generates README.md with project overview, installation, dependencies, and file analysis.
Supports multiple languages (Python, JavaScript, etc.).
Creates visualizations (project structure, dependency graphs, complexity heatmaps).
Excludes irrelevant directories (e.g., .env, venv, node_modules).
Uses t5-small for AI-powered code analysis, with rule-based fallback.

Requirements
Python 3.6+
Optional: matplotlib, networkx, numpy, transformers, torch
Development
bash

git clone https://github.com/yourusername/code_doc_generator
cd code_doc_generator
pip install -r requirements.txt
python -m unittest discover tests
